Exact Traveling Salesman Problem (TSP). Given N cities and
a distance matrix D (Scott list of Scott lists of Scott
nats), find the minimum total distance of a Hamiltonian
cycle that visits every city exactly once and returns to
the start.

@main takes two arguments: a Scott nat N (number of
cities) and the NÃN distance matrix D, where D[i][j] is
the distance from city i to city j. Distances may be
asymmetric. Return the minimum tour cost as a Scott nat.

